source.name: Final Critical Habitat for the Robust spineflower (Chorizanthe robusta var. robusta)
source.description: Abstract: These data identify the areas (in general) where final critical habitat for the robust spineflower (Chorizanthe robusta var. robusta) occurs. Critical habitat for the species occurs along the coast in Santa Cruz and Monterey counties. In Santa Cruz County, there are six units of critical habitat: units A and B in the City of Santa Cruz, units C and D adjacent to the City of Aptos, unit E near the City of Watsonville, and unit F on Sunset State Beach southwest of Watsonville. In Monterey County unit G is located along the coast from the City of Marina south to the City of Seaside.     Purpose: To provide the user with a graphical representation, viewable within a GIS, of the boundaries of critical habitat as described in the Federal Register volume 67, No. 102 pp. 36822 to 36845.
